quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,106,"They will say, "
  23,107,"Our Lord, remove us from it, and if we were to return [to evil], we would indeed be wrongdoers."
  23,108,"He will say, "
  25,52,"So do not obey the disbelievers, and strive against them with it [i.e., the Qur’ān] a great striving."
  25,53,"And it is He who has released [simultaneously] the two seas [i.e., bodies of water], one fresh and sweet and one salty and bitter, and He placed between them a barrier and prohibiting partition."
  25,54,"And it is He who has created from water [i.e., semen] a human being and made him [a relative by] lineage and marriage. And ever is your Lord competent [concerning creation]."
  26,25,"[Pharaoh] said to those around him, "
  26,26,"[Moses] said, "
  26,27,"[Pharaoh] said,{1} ",footnotes:1:[Angrily addressing those present.]
